---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="sixpack CLI Commands" description="Current sixpack CLI command surface.">
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container prose">
      <p class="eyebrow">CLI</p>
      <h1>Small command surface.</h1>
      <p>
        The CLI is intentionally small while the runtime API and storage engine
        settle.
      </p>

      <h2>Implemented</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>`sixpack --version` or `sixpack -V` prints the CLI version.</li>
        <li>`sixpack help`, `-h`, or `--help` prints usage.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Planned</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>initialize a database directory</li>
        <li>inspect schema and storage status</li>
        <li>rebuild generated indexes</li>
        <li>repair or truncate incomplete final writes</li>
        <li>run focused benchmarks or diagnostics</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
